defaultVendors.description: Panda Express serves gourmet Chinese food made with only the freshest ingredients.
Da Spot Health Foods & Juices offers diverse, healthy and affordable cuisine with a unique take on tasty dishes from around the world.
Le Crêpe Café makes traditional French crêpes, cooked to order in front of customers.

defaultVendors.campusLocation: Athletic Complex, 2nd Floor & Paradise Palms Café
defaultVendors.description: Delicious local and Asian-American fusion cuisine served in big portions at reasonable prices!

Holoholo Grill features healthy, locally grown salads, sandwiches, and grab-and-go items at affordable prices. They are committed to using the freshest island-grown ingredients sourced directly from farmers and fishermen. Grab-and-go, breakfast items, or catering for any sized group are also available!
Traditional super ono ahi & tako poke; always fresh, premium ahi — never frozen! Made to order poke by the pound & poke bowls.

Dunkin’ Donuts in Paradise Palms Cafe will keep Hawaii running with high-quality beverage offerings–including freshly-brewed Hot and Iced Coffees–paired perfectly with delicious donuts, bakery good, sandwiches and more.
Mobile eatery serving Mediterranean cuisine like chicken and lamb kabob as well as with vegan options such as hummus, Israeli salad, falafel, and fresh baked pita made daily.

defaultVendors.campusLocation: Post (Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday) & Krauss Hall (Wednesday)
defaultVendors.description: Kamitoku Ramen specializes in a Tottori-style beef bone ramen.

Local beans, local flavor…your local coffee bar.

The Bean Counter serves up brewed coffee from the Hawaiian Islands and fulfills your caffeinated desires with a full service espresso bar. Feed your growling stomach with a dizzying array of bagels with homemade spreads, or chow down with our savory wraps, healthy salads and sweet treats.

Want a sustainable selection for lunch? Try Govinda’s, which offers a 100% pure vegetarian menu, with items low in cholesterol and mostly organic. They strive to bring you a healthy and delicious meal at the best possible price.

defaultVendors.campusLocation: Rotating between Kennedy Theatre (Monday), Post (Tuesday), Kuykendall (Wednesday), Architecture (Thursday), and Korean Studies (Friday)
defaultVendors.description: Hot Tacos offers authentic Mexican food, prepped and cooked daily from scratch offering tacos, burritos, and quesadillas with meat options like steak, chicken, marinated pork, and shredded beef. They offer a la carte options or lunch plates that include beans and Spanish rice and other add on options like Chili Rellenos and Tamales.
Lasoon offers natural home-cooked Nepali and Indian food for everyone. From a $5 bowl options when you are in a hurry to larger plates to please your appetite.

defaultVendors.campusLocation: Rotating between POST, Kuykendall, Architecture, Korean Studies, and Kennedy Theatre
defaultVendors.description: Sistah Truck serves Korean-inspired local cuisine. Daily menu plate lunches include loco moco, chicken katsu, and Korean-style shoyu chicken. They also serve grab-and-go dishes like bibimbap, gyoza and kimchi bowls. Vegetarian options are available.
